x4freetext: Alpha,N Reactions on Au-197
The Stack was Composed of 20 and 100 Mu-Meters
Foils Adding Up to Atotal Thickness of 0.422 Cm
80 MeV Deutron Beam.
Beam Current of 40 Nanoampere.  10 Min
Irradiation
The Spectra was Taken at Different Times Over a
Period of Four Week.
Monitor Cross Section were Taken from G.Christaller,
Europ. Colloq. On Avf Cyclotron, Eindhoven, 1965
The Intensities of the Photolines were Evaluated
By a Least-Square Fit of Gaussians to the Peaks.
With Data from "Roulette" Code.
Last checking has been done.
The Deutron Energy Straggling was Estimated
To Widen the Incident Energy Width of 0.24 MeV at 80
MeV to About 1.3 MeV in the Low Energy Foils.
Without Taking Into Account Uncertanties in the
Decay Scheme Data, the Experimental Error in the Cross
Sections was Estimated to be Typically in the 12-20%
Region. The Values Derived from Different Gamma-Lines
Of the Same Nucleus, However, are not Always Consistent
And Vary by Up to 25%. This Indicates That
Uncertainties in the Decay Scheme Data Contribute
Considerably to the Total Error. The Final Results are
Weighted Averages of the Cross Sections Derived from
Different Gamma-Lines. Though the Total Error of the
Absolute Cross Sections is About 30%, the Relative
Values Within Each Excitation Function Should be
Correct Within About 10%.
- By Compiler: All Gamma-Ray Intensity were Calculated
By Compiler from Authors` Data For Transition
Intensities and Internal Conversion Coefficients.
